Installing Python :

Preferably install Python 2.7 , 64-bit(unless your laptop is 32-bit.If it is 32-bit,install 32-bit Python)
For Windows --

[64-bit Python 2.7.13] - 
Download file -- https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.13/python-2.7.13.amd64.msi
Just follow the setup instructions.

[32-bit Python 2.7.13] - 
Download file -- https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.13/python-2.7.13.msi
Just follow the setup instructions.

For Linux -- 
The latest versions of CentOS, Fedora, Redhat Enterprise (RHEL) and Ubuntu come with Python 2.7 pre-installed.


Installing Numpy :

For Windows --
Download https://sourceforge.net/projects/numpy/files/NumPy/1.8.1/numpy-1.8.1-win32-superpack-python2.7.exe/download
Follow the setup instructions

For Linux -- 
Open Terminal. 
Type these one-by-one:
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
pip install --user numpy scipy matplotlib ipython jupyter pandas sympy nose


Installing OpenCV :

For Windows --
Download https://sourceforge.net/projects/opencvlibrary/files/opencv-win/2.4.13/opencv-2.4.13.exe/download
Extract the downloaded file to C:/ drive.
Now go to the extracted folder named 'opencv',navigate to "C:\opencv\build\python\2.7\x64"
Copy the file cv2.pyd , paste it in C:\Python27\Lib\site-packages.
We're done !

For Linux -- 
sudo apt-get install python2.7-opencv
[Hopefully this should work.It did for us :) ]
its done
